Padova, Italia 
  
 





We propose a generic supersymmetric and
-invariant action for describing coincident D0-branes
with non-abelian matter fields on their worldline. The action is
shown to be in agreement with the Matrix Theory limit of the
ND0-brane effective action. 



Introduction 
The construction of a complete action for the supersymmetric
non-abelian Dirac-Born-Infeld theory which could be associated
with the effective action of the open superstring theory, and the
construction of corresponding supersymmetric actions for
coincident Dirichlet branes is still lacking. At the bosonic level
the problem is that though one knows the full structure of all the
non-abelian terms which enter the effective action under the
symmetrized trace in a DBI manner
, a generic
recipe of constructing the commutator and higher derivative terms
 has not been found yet. Also adding fermionic terms to
the symmetrized trace part of the non-abelian DBI action for
coincident branes via supersymmetrization encounters difficulties.
By now the supersymmetric and -invariant actions with the
symmetrized trace have been constructed only for N coincident
D0-branes (ND0-branes) in , ,
with partial results obtained also for super ND0-branes in a
space-time of arbitrary dimension, and for space
filling ND2-branes in ,  superspace. The
space filling supersymmetric ND2-brane model of has
been constructed with the use of superembedding methods (see
 for a review), while the super ND0-brane models have
been obtained by more traditional methods starting from a
reparametrization invariant form of the bosonic action for N
coincident D0-branes and making it supersymmetric and
-invariant. We shall follow the point of view of above
mentioned papers that N coincident D-branes should, actually, be
regarded as a single brane with non-abelian fields on its
worldvolume, or a N(onabelian)D-brane. The worldvolume
diffeomorphisms and -symmetry of the ND-brane to be
conventional "abelian" symmetries in contrast to the
"non-abelian" proposal of. A main problem of
generalizing these results to higher dimensions is to find an
explicit form of the first-class constraint which is responsible
for the worldline reparametrization invariance of the non-abelian
ND0-brane actions. In a recent paper this problem has
been solved for the case of ND0-branes in  and a worldline
reparametrization invariant bosonic ND0-brane action of
codimension two has been constructed.

The purpose of this paper is to generalize the results of
 and to supersymmetric N
coincident D0-branes in higher dimensional superspaces. The main
result we get is a generic  supersymmetric and -invariant
action for describing coincident D0-branes with non-abelian
matter fields on their worldline. Particular examples to be
considered are the non-abelian ND0-branes in , 
superspace and in type IIA  superspace. The action is
demonstrated to be in agreement with the Matrix Theory limit of
the ND0-brane effective action.



